INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State legislature to adopt legislation amending the State Municipal Home Rule Law (MHRL) to give the City the authority to provide in its Charter that any change in the City’s term limits law must be subject to voter referendum.
EventItemMatterName: Any change in the City’s term limits law must be subject to voter referendum.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass Assembly Bill A7299-B and Senate Bill S3195-C, which would prohibit the writing, sending, or reading of text messages on a hand-held mobile telephone or mobile wireless device while driving.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibit the writing, sending, or reading of text messages on a hand-held mobile telephone or mobile wireless device while driving.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to easily identifiable licenses for vendors.
EventItemMatterName: Easily identifiable licenses for vendors.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Department of Homeless Services to maintain an intake center in Manhattan.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the Department of Homeless Services to maintain an intake center in Manhattan.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to modify the Adam Walsh law, Public Law 109-248, so that it requires background checks for prospective legal guardians or custodians of children.
EventItemMatterName: Modify the Adam Walsh law, Public Law 109-248, so that it requires background checks for prospective legal guardians or custodians of children.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to term limits for elected officials.
EventItemMatterName: Term limits for elected officials.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Veterans
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Human Resources Administration to change its rules to allow Public Administrators to act as organizational friends.
EventItemMatterName: Human Resources Administration to change its rules to allow Public Administrators to act as organizational friends.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to vending in Sunset Park, Brooklyn.
EventItemMatterName: Vending in Sunset Park, Brooklyn.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to creating a small business lease program for establishing an environment for fair negotiations in the commercial lease renewal process in order to determine reasonable lease terms.
EventItemMatterName: Creating a small business lease program for establishing an environment for fair negotiations in the commercial lease renewal process in order to determine reasonable lease terms.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Economic Development
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to regionally significant projects and empire zones.
EventItemMatterName: Regionally significant projects and empire zones.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to creating civil penalties for damaging memorials honoring firefighters, police officers, or armed services members.
EventItemMatterName: Creating civil penalties for damaging memorials honoring firefighters, police officers, or armed services members.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting the use of mobile handsets to text message while driving.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting the use of mobile handsets to text message while driving.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York City Charter in relation to providing that any changes to term limits for elected officers must be submitted for the approval of the electors.
EventItemMatterName: Providing that any changes to term limits for elected officers must be submitted for the approval of the electors.
